10/08/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Romania will support Serbia's position before The Hague-based International Court of Justice (ICJ) in challenging Kosovo's independence, President Traian Basescu said on Sunday (August 9th) during a visit to the Serbian village of Kladovo.
Basescu added that Bucharest will also work to implement Serbia's long-blocked Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU and will help Belgrade get a visa-free regime with the bloc.
(FoNet, B92 - 09/08/09)
